1 sheet ([1] p.)
s.n., [London : 1660]
Verse - "Come lets take the Rump". Imprint from Wing. A ballad, satirizing the Rump. Annotation on Thomason copy: "Feb. 15. 1659". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
